history.content:
CS Kickstart is looking for help!! We are a student organization that aims to empower women in CS at Cal. Our free, week-long summer program introduces incoming freshmen to CS while becoming part of an inclusive community of women in STEM. Due to the current COVID-19 pandemic, this year’s summer program will be completely online, and we need as much help as we can get to facilitate it. 

 

The program will be the week of August 9-15th, but exact dates and times of the program depend on the information we get from this form. 

 

There are several main areas you can help out with: curriculum, social, logistics, and media. 

  • Curriculum includes: developing curriculum, teaching during the week of, lab assisting week of, etc.

  • Social includes: planning social ice breaker and game activities, community building events, etc.

  • Logistics includes: online logistics and technology setup, helping with applications, coordinating faculty/alumni/industry speakers and panels, etc.

  • Media includes: creating graphics, videos, etc.

If there's ANY amount of time that you are willing to put in, please fill out this form by Monday, June 1st, 11:59 PM PDT: https://forms.gle/7scGWMcyhNRSCZx39

 

Also, our application for the 2020 summer program has been released, so if you happen to know any freshmen interested in exploring CS, PLEASE share it with them! Thank you! ❤️ https://forms.gle/2xR6pyFpNNfmRVBd9
history.subject: Want to help incoming freshmen exploring CS in the last week of summer break?
